## Privilege Escalation

![](data:image/png;base64,)  
https://youssef-ichioui.medium.com/abusing-fail2ban-misconfiguration-to-
escalate-privileges-on-linux-826ad0cdafb7  
Michael is part of security group  
![](data:image/png;base64,)  
Security group has read/write on /etc/fail2ban/action.d/ folder  
There is some timing and no shortcuts.  
Deleted original /etc/fail2ban/action.d/iptables-multiport.conf and replaced
it with my own version where the ban action is a nc shell and restarted the
service  
There is a root cron script deleting all of the fail2ban configs apparent
every minute or so.  
![](data:image/png;base64,)  
Gave my replacement script +r permissions  
CMD:

    
    
    rm -rf /etc/fail2ban/action.d/iptables-multiport.conf && cp /home/michael/.tmp/iptables-multipleport.conf /etc/fail2ban/action.d/iptables-multiport.conf && sudo /etc/init.d/fail2ban restar
